This was contained in a press statement issued by the chief press secretary (CPS) to the Governor, Ibrahim Addra, and made available to journalists in Lafia on Tuesday. According to the CPS, the notice of the appointment was contained in a letter signed by the Minister of Communication and Digital Economy, Isa Ibrahim Pantami. Addra explained that the letter indicated that the council was part of effort to implement the National Digital Economy Policy (NDEPS) and the Nigerian E-government Master Plan (NEGMP).